The paper deals with downlink beamforming techniques for joint processing coordinated (JP) multi-point transmission, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithms are based on weighted mean-squared error minimization, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). The paper also discusses transceiver training techniques and user admission, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
